@startuml
' @id(CMP-CYCLE-ORCHESTRATOR)
' @id(CMP-CYCLE-STORE)
' @id(CMP-CORE-CYCLE-MODEL)
' @id(CMP-VIEWER-CYCLE-UI)
' @id(CMP-DIFF-RENDER)
' @ref(USE-RUN-CYCLE)
' @ref(USE-CYCLE-DIFF-VIEW)
' @ref(USE-DIFF-DIAGRAM)
' @ref(DOM-RENDER-ENGINE)
'
' Current-side ownership as built. The skill (markdown) owns
' orchestration + the cycle boundary; mdd-core owns the read model and
' the single Project tree enumeration; the mdd-render engine (driven by
' the `mdd render` mdd-cli subcommand) rasterizes them; mdd-viewer owns
' the tree/diff/description UI; .mdd/cycles/ is the store.
'
' @desc(CMP-CYCLE-ORCHESTRATOR, "Built as the /mdd-cycle skill: templates::MDD_CYCLE_SKILL registered in WORKFLOW_SKILLS, shipped to .claude/ and .codex/skills/mdd-cycle/SKILL.md; its close step rasterizes the cycle diff pumls.")
' @desc(CMP-CYCLE-STORE, "Built as .mdd/cycles/<N>/ on disk (manifest.yml, before/, after/, <diagram>.diff.puml), created by the skill at runtime.")
' @desc(CMP-CORE-CYCLE-MODEL, "Built as crates/mdd-core/src/cycle.rs (incl. Cycle::diff_puml_rel) plus extract_descs and Project::{descriptions,cycle_registry,cycle_diffs,cycle_diff_puml_files}.")
' @desc(CMP-VIEWER-CYCLE-UI, "Built as crates/mdd-viewer/src/tree.rs and the rail/Diff (DiffView, paint_canvas)/DESCRIPTION code in crates/mdd-viewer/src/lib.rs.")
' @desc(CMP-DIFF-RENDER, "Built as the single mdd_render::render_selection engine (render_cycle_diffs is now a thin wrapper over it), invoked through the `mdd render` mdd-cli subcommand (Commands::Render): rasterizes each .mdd/cycles/<N>/<rel>.diff.puml to its .mdd/rendered/cycles/<N>/<rel>.diff.svg mirror. The cycle-close step and the /mdd-render thin-wrapper skill both call `mdd render`; the tree set is the one mdd_core::RenderTree / Project enumeration (DOM-RENDER-ENGINE).")
title Cycle tracking — ownership (current)

actor "Developer" as Dev

component "/mdd-cycle\n(SKILL.md + template)" as Orch
package "existing workflow skills" {
  component "/mdd-generate" as Gen
  component "/mdd-map" as MapS
  component "/mdd-validate" as ValS
  component "/mdd-implement" as ImplS
  component "/mdd-review" as RevS
  component "/mdd-render" as RendS
}

folder ".mdd/cycles/<N>/\nmanifest.yml, before/, after/,\n<rel>.diff.puml" as Store
folder ".mdd/rendered/cycles/<N>/\n<rel>.diff.svg" as Rendered
folder ".mdd/models/, .mdd/trace.yml" as Models

component "mdd-core::cycle + RenderTree\nCycleRegistry, extract_descs,\nProject tree set" as Core
component "mdd render\n(mdd-cli Commands::Render)" as RenderCli
component "mdd-render\nrender_selection (engine)" as DiffRend
component "mdd-viewer\ntree.rs, diff_ui (DiffView),\npaint_canvas, DESCRIPTION" as Viewer
component "eframe / egui 0.30" as Egui

Dev --> Orch : /mdd-cycle [description?]
Orch --> Gen : entry (description given)
Orch --> MapS : entry (no description)
Orch --> ValS : gate
Orch --> ImplS : write code
Orch --> RevS : parity
Orch --> Store : open / before / close / after / diff puml
Orch --> RenderCli : on close, `mdd render`
RendS --> RenderCli : thin wrapper: `mdd render [--only|paths]`
RenderCli --> DiffRend : render_selection(project, sel)
DiffRend --> Core : all_render_sources (RenderTree::ALL, single source)
DiffRend --> Store : read <rel>.diff.puml
DiffRend --> Rendered : write <rel>.diff.svg (rendered_mirror_path)
Gen --> Models : objective + @desc
MapS --> Models : current + @desc

Dev --> Viewer : mdd view
Viewer --> Core : descriptions(), cycle_registry(), cycle_diffs()
Core --> Store : read manifest + snapshots
Core --> Models : scan models + @desc
Viewer --> Rendered : load selected file's <rel>.diff.svg (Diagram sub-mode)
Viewer --> Egui : tree / diff toggle / card widgets
Egui --> Dev : tree rail + Diagram/List diff + description card

note bottom of Orch
  Owns the cycle boundary. Standalone
  /mdd-map and /mdd-generate never open or
  close a cycle (documented in SKILL.md).
end note

note bottom of Rendered
  Viewer has no PlantUML engine; it only
  consumes pre-rendered SVG. Every tree's path
  is a 1:1 mirror (OCL-RENDER-PATH-MIRROR;
  OCL-DIFF-SVG-PATH-DERIVED for the cycle case).
end note
@enduml
